-- Italian Military Pays $1.7 Billion for Finmeccanica Helicopters, Sole Says
-- B y   L o r e n z o   T o t a r o
-- 2010-11-02T07:13:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/italian-military-pays-1-7-billion-for-finmeccanica-helicopters-sole-says.html
 Italy will invest 1.2 billion euros
($1.7 billion) to buy 22 helicopters produced by  Finmeccanica
SpA ’s unit Agusta Westland, Il Sole 24 Ore reported, citing
unidentified sources close to the deal.  The order from the country’s military aviation unit
comprises 10 AW 139 and 12 AW 101 helicopters, the newspaper
said. The investment was approved on Oct. 13 by a parliamentary
defense committee, Sole said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Lorenzo Totaro  in Rome at 
 ltotaro@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
